<br>
You can be friends if and when you both decide that you want that person in your life, but you want nothing else from them.  When you can be genuinely happy about them having a date with someone nice, etc.  <br>
<br>
It takes a lot of time and it doesn't always happen.  <br>
<br>
Don't force it and don't do anything you aren't ready for.  If you can't stand to see him with another girl, you aren't ready for friendship with him yet.  It doesn't mean you don't care, it's just that the wound is still too fresh.<br>
<br>
Take some time.  Maybe go out on a date of your own.  Let your ex know that you need some time before you can be &quot;just a good friend&quot; without feeling uncomfortable with it.  Maybe he feels the same way?<br>
