<br>
So my advice would be to back up for a bit, go out with some girlfriends, have fun, and get used to being without him and having a life separate from him.  Then, when you know you can really look at him as a friend and not want anything more, start hanging out with him again.  <br>
<br>
kemi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uulujainebonelphette.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulujain Ebonelphette</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 814<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/16/02 2:54:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3050.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Time to sever ties; this man may be your ex in reality, but your heart definitely still thinks otherwise.<br>
