<table style="filter:shadow(color=red,strength=2,400"><a href="http://www.ulujain.org">www.ulujain.org</a></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaishen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aishen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 848<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/16/02 11:18:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3050.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> I think the problem is she's rushing it.<br>
<br>
You didn't become an item overnight, you're not going to become friends overnight, either.<br>
<br>
If my husband divorced me, I would be devastated for a time being, I'd allow myself to grieve the end of a relationship I had been a part of, then I'd kick his ass, then I'd get over it, then I'd go date some hot guys, then I'd get laid, then the world would make perfect sense again.<br>
<br>
As awesome as I am, I couldn't be able to do that all in a short period of time.<br>
<br>
Take it slow.  Just because he wants to be friends but you're having a hard time taking the transition doesn't mean there's anything wrong with you.  Just because other people are friends with their exes and you're having a hard time making that happen doesn't mean there's anything wrong with you.  You just have to find your niche.  One thing you do have to do, though, is not cling to something that's gone.  That's where the pain is, from the attachment of something you can't have.<br>
<br>
That being said, can we get back to flaming, raving, ranting, and bitching?  Is group therapy session over yet? <p>- Aishen L`Fey -<br>
